  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "The <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">StreetPainter</code> class declares an instance variable for a 1D array of <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">String</code> values that stores the paint colors a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">StreetPainter</code> object can paint with.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">StreetPainter.java</code>, convert the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">while</code> loop in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">paintMultiLine()</code> method to a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">for</code> loop.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Check out the <strong>Help & Tips</strong> tab ⬆️ for help with traversing a 1D array with a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">for</code> loop.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n## ***Don't forget to . . .***\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/eb2c8910ae2e150019b8e2177405d4af-image-1668191576873.png)\r\n\r\n## 🎯 Goal\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/6be8eba2a31d6c8208fd2bc3a04707cb-image-1674250025486.gif)",
    "mini_rubric": "false",
    "submittable": "false",
    "hide_share_and_remix": "true",
    "csa_view_mode": "neighborhood",
    "reference_links": [
      "/courses/csa-2023/guides/for-loops"
    ],
    "display_name": "The StreetPainter",
    "bubble_choice_description": "Convert the `while` loop to a `for` loop to help the `StreetPainter` paint the street in The Neighborhood.",
